The paper deals with a problem related to computing shortest paths in a subdivision of the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem involves weights associated with the regions, which suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms for optimization (cs.DM). The proof technique involves Galois theory, which is a tool used in theoretical computer science (cs.CC) and algebraic geometry (cs.AG). Finally, the problem of computing shortest paths is related to graph theory (cs.GT).
